Here's the deal, all bodies are beautiful no matter your body size, shape, abs, no abs, jiggle or no jiggle🫶🏼 

I've never been the skinniest person in the room and my body fluctuates between midsize and plus-size. Every so often people comment mean things on my posts -  opinions on other peoples bodies are never anyone's place, and I let them roll off. Why? 

Because my body looks a lot like your bodies🤩

So while I struggle with my own weight, my own personal health and fitness goals, not emotionally eating, wanting my body to look a certain way etc, I want to remind you these few things: 

1. Body weight can be overwhelming. You're not alone in that feeling. Whether you want to gain or lose weight it's hard. I see you. 

2. Life is short, if you want the cake, eat the cake. Seriously depriving yourself isn't healthy either. Moderation honey. You got this. 

3. You want to get surgery, take a supplement, do this or that, to aid in your personal goals? No judgment here. It's your body, your money to spend, and your life.  You do you, boo. 

4. Fitness, health, and body weight are three different things. Fitness is your strength and your endurance. Health is the internal; the things you feed your body and mind with. Body weight; that's just a number on the scale.  Bodies can change throughout your life. Focus on your health babe the rest will fall into place. 

5. Wear the bathing suit, whatever one makes you feel the most confident, and don't miss out on life. There's other women you may inspire just by being YOU✨

Love, your midsize friend

And before anyone comes for me with their ignorance; I am not pushing obesity, unhealthy habits, plastic surgery etc. etc. I'm simply encouraging people to be themselves and make their own choices for THEIR body. If you don't have anything nice to say, don't say it at all🥰

Sharing more of my favorite details from our special day😏

We knew we wanted an unplugged wedding so I created an installation with a phone concierge📞Wedding guests were told beforehand they could either leave their devices in their cars or check it in with our team upon arrival for the duration of our ceremony. I purchased vintage phones off of Amazon. Rented a bar to use as a concierge desk and had a phone booth created. And then, magic happened✨ We had an audio guest book located inside and our loved ones on tape for the rest of our lives. Guests could then retrieve their devices after dinner which meant we truly did mingle with our friends and family. Oh and I obviously had to make a tswift reference. 

What do you think, would you do an unplugged wedding like this? PS our wedding coordinators number was a point of contact for babysitters etc. in case of emergency and guests could step out whenever to use their devices.

Our MIG (most important guest) was a classic bottle of @makersmark ! 

My go-to festive cocktail goes a little like this:

Rosemary Maple Sour: 
1 1/2 parts Maker's Mark 
1/2 part maple syrup 
3/4 part lemon 
2 sprigs of rosemary 

Smack one sprig of rosemary between the palm of your hands and place in strainer. Add the other ingredients and shake with ice. Strain into an ice-filled glass - the large cube opposed to multiple cubes is my favorite😉
Optional: garnish with the remaining sprig and lemon.

Let's talk about my INs for this year 
✨ taking my vitamins daily
✨ hot girl walks with intentional workouts
✨ less alcohol + more water 
✨ eating meals at home 
✨ traveling more for pleasure and work 
✨ not forcing relationships
✨ staying home on the weekends
✨ no phone after 9pm

Here's to a year of filling my cup further and feeling good about it❤️ what things are you wanting to do this new year?!
